# IMDb Explorer — CM3010 Database Coursework

A Node.js/Express web application that queries a local MySQL database of IMDb movie data (2000–2023), answering 5 research questions through interactive data tables and Chart.js visualisations.

---

## Quick Start

### 1. Set up MySQL database
```bash
mysql -u root -p < database/schema.sql
```

### 2. Configure credentials
Edit `.env`:
```
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_mysql_password
DB_NAME=imdb_coursework
PORT=3000
```

### 3. Import IMDb data (streams directly from imdbws.com — no download needed)
```bash
npm run import
```
This takes ~10–20 minutes depending on internet speed. ~80,000 movies will be imported.

### 4. Run the web app
```bash
npm run dev
```
Visit: http://localhost:3000

---

## Project Structure
```
database_project_for_ayaan/
├── app/
│   ├── server.js              # Express entry point
│   ├── db.js                  # MySQL connection pool
│   ├── routes/                # Route handlers (one per research question)
│   ├── views/                 # EJS templates
│   └── public/                # Static CSS and JS
├── database/
│   ├── schema.sql             # CREATE TABLE statements
│   ├── queries.sql            # 5 research question SQL queries
│   └── seed/import.js         # IMDb data importer
├── report/
│   └── screenshots/           # App screenshots for the report
├── .env                       # DB credentials (not committed)
└── package.json
```

## Research Questions
| # | Question |
|---|---|
| RQ1 | Which genres have the highest average IMDb rating? |
| RQ2 | Who are the top 10 directors by average rating (min 5 films)? |
| RQ3 | How has average movie rating changed by year (2000–2023)? |
| RQ4 | Which genres produce the longest movies on average? |
| RQ5 | Which directors work across the most genres? |

## Data Source
IMDb Non-Commercial Datasets — https://datasets.imdbws.com/  
